-- Fifteen Killed as Goods, Passenger Trains Collide in Central Indian State
-- Pradeep Kurup
-- 2010-09-20T06:16:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-20/fifteen-killed-as-goods-passenger-trains-collide-in-central-indian-state.html

          
          
             An empty goods train collided with
a stationary passenger train in the central Indian state of
Madhya Pradesh early today, killing 15 people and injuring 30,
the government said in a statement on the Press Information
Bureau website.  
          
          


  


        